org.anchoranalysis.bean.initializable.property

Class PropertyInitializer<P>

  • Object
    • PropertyInitializer<P>
  • Type Parameters:
    P - init-param type

    public class PropertyInitializer<P>
extends Object
    Tries to initialize a bean's property with particular (or derived) parameters

    Specifically, two types of properties will be initialized:
    • Properties that have identical property-type to P (the current parameters)
    • Properties with another property-type that can be extracted from P (the current parameters)
    Author:
    Owen Feehan

      • applyInitializationIfPossibleTo

        public boolean applyInitializationIfPossibleTo(Object propertyValue,
                                               Object parent,
                                               Logger logger)
                                        throws InitException
        Applies the initialization to a property using the current or extracted params if possible.

        It is essential that setParam(Object) is called before this method

        Parameters:
        propertyValue - bean-property to be initialized (as a root)
        parent - the parent bean in which this property resides
        logger - logger for any errrors
        Returns:
        true if some kind of initialization occurred with this property, false otherwise
        Throws:
        InitException
